Explanation:
We iterate from 10 to n using a for loop, incrementing the count variable with each iteration. After that, we return count - (n % 10) to get the nth digit. The time complexity is O(log(n)) because we only need to iterate log(n) times to find the nth digit. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the count variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm has a negligible impact on energy consumption.

